Class Source.Redirect

  • com.stripe.android.model.Source.Redirect
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StripeModel
    Enclosing class:
    Source

    public static class Source.Redirect
implements StripeModel

    Information related to the redirect flow. Present if the source is authenticated by a redirect (flow is Flow.Redirect).

    • Constructor Detail

      • Redirect

        public Redirect(@Nullable
                java.lang.String returnUrl,
                @Nullable
                com.stripe.android.model.Source.Redirect.Status status,
                @Nullable
                java.lang.String url)

        Information related to the redirect flow. Present if the source is authenticated by a redirect (flow is Flow.Redirect).

        Parameters:
        returnUrl - The URL you provide to redirect the customer to after they authenticated their payment.
        status - The status of the redirect, eitherpending (ready to be used by your customer to authenticate the transaction),succeeded (succesful authentication, cannot be reused) ornot_required (redirect should not be used) orfailed (failed authentication, cannot be reused).
        url - The URL provided to you to redirect a customer to as part of a redirectauthentication flow.
